    "source_detail": "Reiner & Rubinstein (1991), 'Breaking Down the Barriers', Risk Magazine 4(8), 28-35. Down-and-out call formula with H=1 (barrier far below S=100) reduces to the vanilla Black-Scholes call: C_do(H->0) = C_BS. Reference computed via standard BS formula: d1=(ln(S/K)+(r+sigma^2/2)*T)/(sigma*sqrt(T))=0.35, d2=0.15, N(d1)=0.63683, N(d2)=0.55962, C=S*N(d1)-K*exp(-r*T)*N(d2)=10.450583572185565 per unit notional. Parameters: S=K=100, H=1, T=1y Act365F (2026-04-30 to 2027-04-30), r=5%, q=0%, sigma=20%.",
